"""Async mirror of `cursor_sdk._client`.

`AsyncClient`, `AsyncAgent`, `AsyncRun`, `AsyncCursor` mirror the public sync
API. The two paths share serializers from `types.py`, error parsing from
`errors.py`, and the cloud remote-bridge guard helpers from `_client.py`.

Design choices:

- No global async default client. Async users instantiate `AsyncClient`
  explicitly or use `AsyncClient.launch_bridge(...)` as an async context
  manager. This avoids cross-event-loop bugs from sharing a global handle.
- Async streams expose `__aiter__`. `await run.wait()` drains the stream
  before falling back to the unary `WaitLiveRun` RPC, mirroring the sync
  behavior.
- `on_delta` / `on_step` callbacks may be sync or async; if the return value
  is awaitable, it is awaited inline so events stay ordered.
"""

